26/01/2004
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- A two-day session of the Macedonian-EU inter-parliamentary committee was held in Brussels, MIA reported Friday (23 January).
Participants discussed the progress achieved by the Macedonian government in judicial reform and fighting corruption.
The EU representatives also praised the results of the national census, conducted in 2002.
However, they expressed concern over the low standard of living, the high unemployment rate and the significant presence of a gray economy.
(MIA, A1 TV - 23/01/04)
